### 1. One-Line Summary

Rakza 7 is the more balanced, easier, and more all-around offensive rubber, while Etika Pro H is the harder, more spin-loaded, more demanding option with better precision under stronger commitment.

### 2. Head-to-Head Breakdown

* **Speed & Gears:**
    * **Low Impact:** Rakza 7 is easier to access in the short-to-medium swing range. It gives you usable pace without needing perfect body commitment. Etika Pro H feels firmer and a bit deader at light impact, so it rewards cleaner engagement more than casual touch acceleration.
    * **Top End:** Etika Pro H has the higher ceiling when you swing through the ball properly. Its harder sponge gives it more authority on full topspins and power counters. Rakza 7 is still plenty offensive, but its top gear is less imposing.
    * **Linearity:** Etika Pro H feels more linear and honest through the stroke once you engage it. Rakza 7 has a more accessible built-in response, which feels easier, but slightly less locked in at maximum effort.

* **Spin Mechanics:**
    * **Opening Loop:** Rakza 7 is easier for opening against backspin because it bites the ball more easily with less precision required. Etika Pro H can produce a heavier opening ball, but only if your timing and acceleration are good enough to fully engage the harder sponge.
    * **Max Spin:** Etika Pro H has the advantage in peak spin potential, especially on committed forehand loops and power topspins. Rakza 7 still produces strong spin, but it is more easy spin than heaviest possible spin.
    * **Topsheet Grip:** Both are grippy offensive rubbers, but Etika Pro H feels more focused on high-friction, power-oriented grip. Rakza 7s grip is excellent, yet it is packaged in a more forgiving overall tuning.

* **Flight Path (Throw Angle):**
    * **Arc Height:** Rakza 7 generally gives the easier, safer arc in standard topspin exchanges. Etika Pro Hs trajectory is more controlled and direct when driven properly, but it does not help as much if your contact is late or passive.
    * **Safety:** Rakza 7 offers more natural clearance and is safer for varied levels of timing quality. Etika Pro H becomes very safe in the hands of a confident attacker, but it is less forgiving mechanically.

* **Feel & Feedback:**
    * **Sensation:** Rakza 7 feels more elastic, more lively, and more immediately user-friendly. Etika Pro H feels harder, firmer, and more compact at contact, with a more serious performance rubber character.
    * **Dwell:** Rakza 7 gives the clearer sensation of holding and lifting the ball in normal offensive play. Etika Pro H has less apparent dwell at soft impact, but at stronger engagement it gives a very secure, loaded contact.

* **Control & Short Game:**
    * **Sensitivity:** Rakza 7 is the easier rubber for most players in general rally control. Etika Pro H is not uncontrollable, but because of the harder sponge and more demanding contact, it asks for better hands and cleaner bat angle management.
    * **Touch Play:** Etika Pro H can be very precise in pushes, punch touches, and short placement if you are technically clean. Rakza 7 is easier for more players because it feels less exacting and more intuitive in mixed-tempo play.

* **Blocking & Countering:**
    * **Passive Block:** Etika Pro H has the edge in firmness and directional stability on passive blocks, especially against stronger incoming pace. Rakza 7 blocks well too, but feels a bit more reactive and less solid wall under pressure.
    * **Active Counter:** Etika Pro H is stronger here for advanced attackers. The harder sponge gives better confidence on committed counter-topspins and punchier re-acceleration. Rakza 7 is still very competent, but not as authoritative.

### 3. The Recommendation

* **Choose Rakza 7 if:**
    * You want the more balanced and versatile rubber.
    * You value easier opening loops, easier arc, and better access to performance at medium effort.
    * You want a rubber that works well on both forehand and backhand for a wide range of offensive styles.
    * You prefer a classic high-quality grippy tensor feel without needing a very hard sponge.

* **Choose Etika Pro H if:**
    * You want a harder, more direct, more spin-focused attacking rubber.
    * You play with stronger technique and can consistently compress a hard sponge.
    * You prioritize power loop quality, counter-topspin stability, and precise blocking.
    * You are willing to trade some forgiveness and ease for higher top-end performance.
